    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Machine screws that are permanently combined with a lock washer which was inserted before the thread was cut. The term probably derives from an abbreviation for “assemblies,” because the screw and washer are pre-assembled when purchased.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
